    Hi Tal,<br>
    <br>
    The released Windows binaries are built only for Microsoft VS
    compilers. <br>
    <br>
    If you want to use gcc and g++, you have to build Open MPI by
    yourself using CMake.&nbsp; Just select "MSYS Makefiles" as the
    generator, you can build binaries under MinGW. Please note that,
    this is only supported for 32bit MinGW, and there may be run-time
    problems, as it is still experimental.<br>
    <br>
    <br>
    Regards,<br>
    Shiqing<br>
    <br>
